SECTION 3 — ARCHITECTURE RULES (NON-NEGOTIABLE)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
PPUK v7 uses the following architecture requirements:

### FRONTEND (V0 / Next.js 14 / React 18)
- TypeScript strict mode ON
- Tailwind + shadcn/ui ONLY
- React Query for all server state
- Component-per-file architecture
- Folder layout:
  ```
  /src/app
  /src/components/ui
  /src/components/business
  /src/components/property
  /src/components/api-preview
  /src/hooks
  /src/lib
  /src/types
  /src/api
  ```
- No inline styles
- No CSS modules
- No Redux
- No untyped fetch calls
- No client-side secrets

### BACKEND (Supabase + Edge Functions)
- Database access via Supabase client (typed)
- ALL external APIs must run in Edge Functions
- ALL user-data tables protected by RLS
- API keys NEVER exposed to frontend
- RPC functions require row-level policy checks
- x-supabase-auth header required on sensitive functions

### DOCUMENTS AND MEDIA
- Storage buckets:
  - property-documents
  - property-photos
- Uploads go through validation
- Signed URLs used for download
- No public storage unless explicitly documented

### ERROR HANDLING
- Safe error messages only
- No leaking stack traces
- UI uses toast + boundary patterns

### TESTING
- Every business component must have tests
- All API functions must have integration tests
- No merging without test pass

